1
00:00:00,391 --> 00:00:02,960
(One day in January with everything covered with snow)

2
00:00:02,961 --> 00:00:04,760
- I need to go there.
- Hee Chul!

3
00:00:04,761 --> 00:00:06,231
- What?
- Hee Chul... What?

4
00:00:06,831 --> 00:00:08,800
Did Hee Chul get expelled? Did he transfer to another school?

5
00:00:08,801 --> 00:00:09,830
- It's just between us...
- No.

6
00:00:09,831 --> 00:00:11,160
Did Hee Chul transfer to another school?

7
00:00:11,161 --> 00:00:12,770
- He's on an overseas concert tour.
- Overseas concert tour.

8
00:00:12,771 --> 00:00:14,470
- He's making money overseas.
- He's in another country now.

9
00:00:14,471 --> 00:00:17,670
Is he on a trip or a concert tour? We should confirm the truth.

10
00:00:17,671 --> 00:00:19,010
It's for his world tour concert.

11
00:00:19,011 --> 00:00:21,940
The world tour concert is continuing.

12
00:00:21,941 --> 00:00:23,880
- If he's on his concert tour, - So it hasn't ended.

13
00:00:23,881 --> 00:00:25,880
I will move to the front row.

14
00:00:25,881 --> 00:00:28,850
But I... Why would Sang Min sit there?

15
00:00:28,851 --> 00:00:30,581
He does everything as he wants because he won the Grand Award.

16
00:00:31,851 --> 00:00:33,120
Exactly.

17
00:00:33,121 --> 00:00:34,551
Because he won the Grand Award,

18
00:00:35,061 --> 00:00:36,620
- he switched seats as he wanted.
- Congratulations.

19
00:00:36,621 --> 00:00:38,561
- The Grand Award...
- At the Entertainment Awards...

20
00:00:38,961 --> 00:00:40,531
What? A girl is here.

21
00:00:40,931 --> 00:00:42,161
(A girl is here.)

22
00:00:42,401 --> 00:00:43,460
- Is he Hee Chul?
- Oh, what?

23
00:00:43,461 --> 00:00:45,070
- Hee Chul...
- Who is that?

24
00:00:45,071 --> 00:00:49,140
- Whoever that is...
- Brother Woo Il is here.

25
00:00:49,141 --> 00:00:52,741
- Who is that?
- Brother Woo Il is here.

26
00:00:52,811 --> 00:00:54,570
(He brings up the energy with his specialty from the start.)

27
00:00:54,571 --> 00:00:55,810
- He's so energetic.
- Keep going.

28
00:00:55,811 --> 00:00:58,111
Nice.

29
00:00:58,951 --> 00:01:00,751
It's good to see you again. It's been a while.

30
00:01:00,881 --> 00:01:02,520
- I'm glad you're here, Woo Il.
- What brings you here?

31
00:01:02,521 --> 00:01:04,680
I heard Hee Chul would be absent today.

32
00:01:04,681 --> 00:01:06,290
- So I'll sit in his seat.
- Did Hee Chul tell you that?

33
00:01:06,291 --> 00:01:07,390
What? Okay.

34
00:01:07,391 --> 00:01:08,460
- All right.
- May I sit here?

35
00:01:08,461 --> 00:01:09,461
- Okay.
- What's going on?

36
00:01:09,462 --> 00:01:11,220
- He's sitting in Sang Min's seat?
- Sang Min is coming back?

37
00:01:11,221 --> 00:01:12,290
You don't mind, do you?

38
00:01:12,291 --> 00:01:13,860
- Sure. You can sit there, Woo Il.
- Thank you.

39
00:01:13,861 --> 00:01:15,630
- The Grand Award winner lost.
- Right.

40
00:01:15,631 --> 00:01:16,930
- To be honest, - He came back to his seat.

41
00:01:16,931 --> 00:01:21,101
winning the award is the best thing that happened recently.

42
00:01:21,671 --> 00:01:25,941
And I believe Ho Dong is the one who made it possible.

43
00:01:26,641 --> 00:01:28,180
- But you didn't mention him.
- Here's why.

44
00:01:28,181 --> 00:01:29,710
- Why?
- He didn't mention Ho Dong at all.

45
00:01:29,711 --> 00:01:32,811
- That's right.
- Ho Dong gave me a big hug.

46
00:01:35,281 --> 00:01:38,751
(You need to give me a hug.)

47
00:01:39,351 --> 00:01:43,521
(Ho Dong gave Sang Min a big hug.)

48
00:01:43,721 --> 00:01:44,990
I asked him for a hug...

49
00:01:44,991 --> 00:01:47,931
so that I could receive good energy, which would bring me good luck.

50
00:01:48,431 --> 00:01:51,360
- But I was sure it'd be Jang Hoon.
- Ho Dong gave him a hug.

51
00:01:51,361 --> 00:01:53,430
So I kept looking at Jang Hoon...

52
00:01:53,431 --> 00:01:54,431
to congratulate him.

53
00:01:54,631 --> 00:01:55,670
But my name was called.

54
00:01:55,671 --> 00:01:57,500
That means good luck came to me.

55
00:01:57,501 --> 00:01:59,070
(But Sang Min won the Grand Award.)

56
00:01:59,071 --> 00:02:01,440
- Thanks to Ho Dong's hug, - Why did you give him a hug?

57
00:02:01,441 --> 00:02:02,540
I was honored with the award.

58
00:02:02,541 --> 00:02:04,140
Oh, my goodness.

59
00:02:04,141 --> 00:02:05,950
- I'm grateful that he thinks that.
- Thanks to Ho Dong...

60
00:02:05,951 --> 00:02:07,280
Sang Min received Ho Dong's energy...

61
00:02:07,281 --> 00:02:08,620
- and won the Grand Award.
- That's right.

62
00:02:08,621 --> 00:02:10,350
- Ho Dong's energy made it possible.
- He helped me win the Grand Award.

63
00:02:10,351 --> 00:02:12,450
By the way, won't there be any transfer students today?

64
00:02:12,451 --> 00:02:13,920
- What?
- What?

65
00:02:13,921 --> 00:02:15,421
- What?
- What?

66
00:02:16,091 --> 00:02:18,460
- Oh, my. "Sing Again 4!"
- Hey, run.

67
00:02:18,461 --> 00:02:20,591
- "Sing Again 4!"
- Guys, let's go!

68
00:02:25,101 --> 00:02:28,970
(They enter with unusually cheerful energy.)

69
00:02:28,971 --> 00:02:31,270
(Amazed)

70
00:02:31,271 --> 00:02:32,671
This is amazing.

71
00:02:33,171 --> 00:02:35,680
(The top 7 of "Sing Again 4" are here.)

72
00:02:35,681 --> 00:02:37,510
It hasn't been so long since the show ended.

73
00:02:37,511 --> 00:02:38,511
That's right.

74
00:02:38,512 --> 00:02:41,081
- Let them introduce themselves.
- This is awesome.

75
00:02:41,951 --> 00:02:44,351
We should do that first. Which school did you transfer from?

76
00:02:44,681 --> 00:02:48,561
Hi. We're from We Want To Be Famous Singers High School.

77
00:02:48,791 --> 00:02:50,760
I'm the phoenix of "Sing Again 4."

78
00:02:50,761 --> 00:02:52,190
I'm Kim Ye Chan, the seventh place.

79
00:02:52,191 --> 00:02:53,191
Ye Chan!

80
00:02:54,031 --> 00:02:55,200
Ye Chan!

81
00:02:55,201 --> 00:02:59,130
Hi. I'm the resilient one of "Sing Again 4."

82
00:02:59,131 --> 00:03:01,201
I'm KYURI, the sixth place.

83
00:03:02,271 --> 00:03:04,400
- She's so cute. KYURI!
- Indeed.

84
00:03:04,401 --> 00:03:06,471
Hi. On "Sing Again 4,"

85
00:03:06,771 --> 00:03:08,881
I was called the crazy one. I'm sEODo.

86
00:03:09,811 --> 00:03:11,711
- He sang "Red Dragonfly."
- sEODo.

87
00:03:12,611 --> 00:03:14,181
I'm the genius and the youngest...

88
00:03:14,281 --> 00:03:16,750
of "Sing Again 4." I'm slowly.

89
00:03:16,751 --> 00:03:17,851
slowly!

90
00:03:18,851 --> 00:03:20,250
- slowly!
- Hi.

91
00:03:20,251 --> 00:03:23,090
I placed 3rd on "Sing Again 4."

92
00:03:23,091 --> 00:03:25,731
I'm Kim Jae Min, the ambitious singer.

93
00:03:26,691 --> 00:03:27,790
One must have ambition.

94
00:03:27,791 --> 00:03:29,831
That's right. One must have ambition.

95
00:03:30,361 --> 00:03:33,571
I was reborn in Korea through "Sing Again 4."

96
00:03:33,931 --> 00:03:35,741
I placed second. I'm Dorado.

97
00:03:36,601 --> 00:03:39,210
- Welcome, Dorado!
- Dorado!

98
00:03:39,211 --> 00:03:41,010
- The winner!
- Dorado

99
00:03:41,011 --> 00:03:42,780
- Dorado - Stop it.

100
00:03:42,781 --> 00:03:44,541
- Dorado - Hey.

101
00:03:46,711 --> 00:03:49,850
Hi. I'm the icon of growth from "Sing Again 4..."

102
00:03:49,851 --> 00:03:53,221
and the winner of the competition. I'm Lee Oh Ouk.

103
00:03:53,321 --> 00:03:54,790
(They're here to take over Brother School!)

104
00:03:54,791 --> 00:03:56,621
A-e-i-o-u, Lee Oh Ouk.

105
00:03:57,021 --> 00:04:01,091
(There were the most applicants in the history of "Sing Again.")

106
00:04:01,861 --> 00:04:05,201
(The top 7 participants)

107
00:04:05,531 --> 00:04:09,101
(Kim Ye Chan returned with a more powerful voice.)

108
00:04:09,541 --> 00:04:11,300
(She was in a wheelchair in the beginning.)

109
00:04:11,301 --> 00:04:13,641
(But KYURI stands on her own feet now.)

110
00:04:13,941 --> 00:04:17,911
(Beyond Joseon pop, sEODo showed us a new world.)

111
00:04:18,141 --> 00:04:23,621
(slowly, the youngest contestant, has such a great singing ability.)

112
00:04:23,951 --> 00:04:27,791
(Kim Jae Min was full of confidence even from the beginning.)

113
00:04:27,921 --> 00:04:32,491
(Dorado got the highest score on "Sing Again 4.")

114
00:04:32,761 --> 00:04:36,861
(Lee Oh Ouk, the winner, sublimated life into rock music.)

115
00:04:37,131 --> 00:04:39,401
(The top 7 of "Sing Again 4")

116
00:04:39,631 --> 00:04:41,940
(They transferred to Brother School.)

117
00:04:41,941 --> 00:04:43,941
- He's the winner!
- Welcome, everyone!

118
00:04:44,601 --> 00:04:46,310
- Thank you.
- The top seven.

119
00:04:46,311 --> 00:04:48,040
The viewers must not know this.

120
00:04:48,041 --> 00:04:49,680
- Today, the day of the recording, - Right.

121
00:04:49,681 --> 00:04:51,310
is Thursday, and two days ago,

122
00:04:51,311 --> 00:04:52,850
- On Tuesday.
- the final live show was aired.

123
00:04:52,851 --> 00:04:54,110
- That's right.
- Correct.

124
00:04:54,111 --> 00:04:55,450
You guys came here almost right after that.

125
00:04:55,451 --> 00:04:56,580
- Yes, it was only two days ago.
- Right.

126
00:04:56,581 --> 00:04:59,690
Oh Ouk, it must've felt like a dream when the winner was announced.

127
00:04:59,691 --> 00:05:01,350
You must've been out of it.

128
00:05:01,351 --> 00:05:02,690
Have you snapped out of it yet?

129
00:05:02,691 --> 00:05:05,060
- I haven't quite snapped out of it.
- It still feels like a dream?

130
00:05:05,061 --> 00:05:06,990
- Are you confused?
- I'm still a bit out of it.

131
00:05:06,991 --> 00:05:08,560
Oh Ouk, did you expect to win the competition?

132
00:05:08,561 --> 00:05:11,330
The score gap between you and the runner-up was 41 points.

133
00:05:11,331 --> 00:05:13,470
- He won with a small margin.
- That's right.

134
00:05:13,471 --> 00:05:14,570
- A 41-point margin is really small.
- That's a small margin.

135
00:05:14,571 --> 00:05:15,571
- Is that so?
- Including SMS voting. Yes.

136
00:05:15,871 --> 00:05:19,210
(The final score gap)

137
00:05:19,211 --> 00:05:22,580
(The final score gap: 41 points)

138
00:05:22,581 --> 00:05:29,880
(The winner of "Sing Again 4" was Lee Oh Ouk.)

139
00:05:29,881 --> 00:05:33,550
The winner of "Sing Again 4..."

140
00:05:33,551 --> 00:05:35,761
is Singer Lee Oh Ouk.

141
00:05:37,291 --> 00:05:42,830
(The prize money for the winner: 300,000 dollars)

142
00:05:42,831 --> 00:05:43,860
Actually...

143
00:05:43,861 --> 00:05:45,900
After we finished our final performances,

144
00:05:45,901 --> 00:05:47,470
I placed fourth...

145
00:05:47,471 --> 00:05:49,040
- based on the judges' scores.
- Right.

146
00:05:49,041 --> 00:05:50,700
To be honest, I gave up hope then.

147
00:05:50,701 --> 00:05:52,310
- I didn't think I had a chance.
- Right.

148
00:05:52,311 --> 00:05:53,970
So after Jae Min was announced to be the third place,

149
00:05:53,971 --> 00:05:55,511
the two of us were left. And I thought,

150
00:05:55,941 --> 00:05:57,880
"This is weird. How did this happen?"

151
00:05:57,881 --> 00:05:59,480
I was chosen as the winner thanks to the result of the voting.

152
00:05:59,481 --> 00:06:00,551
I was grateful.

153
00:06:01,251 --> 00:06:02,950
- So you didn't expect it?
- No, I didn't expect it at all.

154
00:06:02,951 --> 00:06:04,080
You turned the tables.

155
00:06:04,081 --> 00:06:05,951
Sang Min didn't expect to win the Grand Award either.

156
00:06:07,221 --> 00:06:09,320
- Congratulations.
- Congratulations.

157
00:06:09,321 --> 00:06:11,390
(Congratulations on winning the Grand Award.)

158
00:06:11,391 --> 00:06:14,930
We're with the Grand Award winner and the winner of "Sing Again 4."

159
00:06:14,931 --> 00:06:16,030
(As if it were a summit meeting)

160
00:06:16,031 --> 00:06:17,701
They just won those titles.

161
00:06:18,901 --> 00:06:20,800
- It happened so recently.
- Indeed.

162
00:06:20,801 --> 00:06:22,940
- Just recently.
- Exactly.

163
00:06:22,941 --> 00:06:24,601
- It's incredible!
- It happened just recently.

164
00:06:26,371 --> 00:06:28,611
- But from Dorado's perspective...
- Right.

165
00:06:29,611 --> 00:06:30,841
I'm so jealous.

166
00:06:32,011 --> 00:06:33,981
I wanted to win 300,000 dollars too.

167
00:06:35,051 --> 00:06:36,420
- That's right.
- She's being honest.

168
00:06:36,421 --> 00:06:37,950
With a 41-point margin,

169
00:06:37,951 --> 00:06:39,190
you lost your chance to win it. How much did you receive?

170
00:06:39,191 --> 00:06:40,520
- We received 30,000 dollars.
- We received 30,000 dollars.

171
00:06:40,521 --> 00:06:42,490
- Both the 2nd and 3rd did, right?
- Correct.

172
00:06:42,491 --> 00:06:43,961
All you thought about was the money you could've won?

173
00:06:45,731 --> 00:06:47,290
But I received a sofa as well,

174
00:06:47,291 --> 00:06:48,291
- so I was okay.
- Right. We received a sofa too.

175
00:06:48,292 --> 00:06:49,860
- A sofa was also a prize.
- I was okay.

176
00:06:49,861 --> 00:06:51,730
- You're okay.
- It's an expensive one.

177
00:06:51,731 --> 00:06:55,540
- "Sing Again 4..."
- Still, Dorado and Jae Min...

178
00:06:55,541 --> 00:06:57,641
received prize money.

179
00:06:57,871 --> 00:07:01,340
But as for the youngest contestant, you performed in the final round,

180
00:07:01,341 --> 00:07:02,610
but you didn't receive anything, right?

181
00:07:02,611 --> 00:07:04,210
- Really?
- The fourth place didn't receive...

182
00:07:04,211 --> 00:07:05,950
- prize money or a sofa.
- Oh, gosh.

183
00:07:05,951 --> 00:07:08,680
- The three of them got a banner.
- Right.

184
00:07:08,681 --> 00:07:10,681
Only I was standing with empty hands.

185
00:07:11,321 --> 00:07:13,020
- I feel bad.
- Right.

186
00:07:13,021 --> 00:07:14,350
- If you feel bad, give me the sofa.
- She...

187
00:07:14,351 --> 00:07:15,420
- Come on.
- She...

188
00:07:15,421 --> 00:07:18,090
In a contest like that, you must compete fairly.

189
00:07:18,091 --> 00:07:19,560
- That's right.
- But since it's a competition...

190
00:07:19,561 --> 00:07:20,760
Have you ever hoped another contestant would...

191
00:07:20,761 --> 00:07:22,900
- Make a mistake?
- make a mistake?

192
00:07:22,901 --> 00:07:25,000
- What a realistic question.
- Be honest with us.

193
00:07:25,001 --> 00:07:26,030
- Well, I have.
- It's understandable.

194
00:07:26,031 --> 00:07:27,230
Right. You hope for that. It's natural.

195
00:07:27,231 --> 00:07:28,231
- Right.
- It's a competition.

196
00:07:28,232 --> 00:07:29,540
Dorado said she had hoped for it.

197
00:07:29,541 --> 00:07:31,870
Dorado and I competed against each other in one round.

198
00:07:31,871 --> 00:07:33,270
- Oh, that's right.
- I didn't know you hoped for that.

199
00:07:33,271 --> 00:07:35,610
No. I didn't hope for it. It's not like that.

200
00:07:35,611 --> 00:07:37,480
- She put her on the spot.
- Hang on.

201
00:07:37,481 --> 00:07:39,380
- KYURI put her on the spot.
- Right.

202
00:07:39,381 --> 00:07:40,910
- KYURI, - That's right.

203
00:07:40,911 --> 00:07:43,050
when you had a 1-on-1 match with Dorado,

204
00:07:43,051 --> 00:07:46,521
did you hope she'd perform at her very best without making a mistake?

205
00:07:46,891 --> 00:07:47,891
Of course.

206
00:07:48,961 --> 00:07:51,460
- You don't sound like you mean it.
- It could've sounded more sincere.

207
00:07:51,461 --> 00:07:52,891
You are very great.

208
00:07:54,431 --> 00:07:57,200
Actually, Dorado is such a great singer.

209
00:07:57,201 --> 00:07:59,530
- Indeed.
- So I couldn't even imagine...

210
00:07:59,531 --> 00:08:01,770
- she would make a mistake.
- Right.

211
00:08:01,771 --> 00:08:03,300
- Dorado is a great singer.
- You can't even imagine it.

212
00:08:03,301 --> 00:08:05,101
Jae Min was the one who made a mistake.

213
00:08:05,641 --> 00:08:08,071
- You... What was that?
- Hey, don't talk about it.

214
00:08:08,241 --> 00:08:12,250
(While performing a new song in the final round...)

215
00:08:12,251 --> 00:08:16,251
(While performing a new song in the final round...)

216
00:08:18,851 --> 00:08:22,760
(Before the sun rises)

217
00:08:22,761 --> 00:08:26,591
(Before the sun rises)

218
00:08:28,861 --> 00:08:31,100
- You... What was that?
- Hey, don't talk about it.

219
00:08:31,101 --> 00:08:32,801
Did you not want to place first?

220
00:08:33,371 --> 00:08:35,500
- Me?
- What was the reason? Yes.

221
00:08:35,501 --> 00:08:37,640
- I wanted to place first so badly.
- Then why...

222
00:08:37,641 --> 00:08:40,511
Since it had been a long battle,

223
00:08:40,811 --> 00:08:42,581
I guess my body got tired.

224
00:08:42,881 --> 00:08:44,911
I woke up and felt refreshed.

225
00:08:45,411 --> 00:08:46,810
- But my throat wasn't feeling well.
- Because you were nervous.

226
00:08:46,811 --> 00:08:48,280
- That happens. You slept well, - Nervousness can cause it.

227
00:08:48,281 --> 00:08:50,151
- but you don't feel so well.
- But Jae Min.

228
00:08:50,281 --> 00:08:51,950
It was okay that you made a mistake.

229
00:08:51,951 --> 00:08:54,620
But you totally failed to maintain your composure.

230
00:08:54,621 --> 00:08:56,090
- But still...
- It was so easy for the judges...

231
00:08:56,091 --> 00:08:57,821
to tell that you made a mistake.

232
00:08:58,291 --> 00:09:00,530
- You should've remained confident, - Right.

233
00:09:00,531 --> 00:09:02,500
but you made it so obvious that you made a mistake.

234
00:09:02,501 --> 00:09:03,930
- Oh, dear.
- Above all,

235
00:09:03,931 --> 00:09:07,271
I wanted to remember the moment,

236
00:09:07,401 --> 00:09:11,440
I was focusing more on the audience than singing.

237
00:09:11,441 --> 00:09:13,640
You guys competed in a studio in this building.

238
00:09:13,641 --> 00:09:15,210
- Yes.
- It was in this very building.

239
00:09:15,211 --> 00:09:18,510
- Why don't you redeem yourself?
- Sounds great.

240
00:09:18,511 --> 00:09:20,380
How about you sing the song here?

241
00:09:20,381 --> 00:09:22,321
- Sounds great. You're right.
- He'll sing it here.

242
00:09:22,551 --> 00:09:24,080
- Let's go, Jae Min!
- Let's go!

