00:29:04,601 --> 00:29:06,030
- I did, and...
- Yes?

724
00:29:06,031 --> 00:29:07,871
I was shaking until I had the mike in my hands,

725
00:29:08,231 --> 00:29:09,701
but as soon as I started, I wasn't nervous anymore.

726
00:29:10,071 --> 00:29:11,870
- So it was fascinating to me.
- It's your road to take.

727
00:29:11,871 --> 00:29:16,071
Afterwards, the sounds of the guitar and drums felt so cool to me,

728
00:29:16,371 --> 00:29:18,110
and I felt like I wanted to try it.

729
00:29:18,111 --> 00:29:20,150
That's how I got into it.

730
00:29:20,151 --> 00:29:21,750
You weren't nervous?

731
00:29:21,751 --> 00:29:23,950
Back in our days, the band club had...

732
00:29:23,951 --> 00:29:25,780
- the peak popularity.
- That's right.

733
00:29:25,781 --> 00:29:27,390
They became insanely popular during school festivals.

734
00:29:27,391 --> 00:29:29,120
When you were in school, Oh Ouk,

735
00:29:29,121 --> 00:29:30,690
how popular was the band club?

736
00:29:30,691 --> 00:29:33,090
I think the band club was the most popular.

737
00:29:33,091 --> 00:29:34,260
Is it still like that?

738
00:29:34,261 --> 00:29:35,660
- Was it a co-ed school?
- Yes.

739
00:29:35,661 --> 00:29:36,730
- That's why.
- I see.

740
00:29:36,731 --> 00:29:37,731
If it were an all-boys school,

741
00:29:37,731 --> 00:29:38,731
- they wouldn't even get a glance.
- If it were an all-boys school,

742
00:29:38,731 --> 00:29:39,731
it would have been tough.

743
00:29:39,732 --> 00:29:41,831
He might not have even applied if it were all boys.

744
00:29:42,601 --> 00:29:43,770
- Of course.
- Is that necessary?

745
00:29:43,771 --> 00:29:45,771
- That's true.
- What would he do that for?

746
00:29:46,671 --> 00:29:47,840
You're right.

747
00:29:47,841 --> 00:29:49,340
He would rather go to the karaoke.

748
00:29:49,341 --> 00:29:51,740
- But it might be his beginning.
- Right.

749
00:29:51,741 --> 00:29:54,110
Oh Ouk, when you're in a band,

750
00:29:54,111 --> 00:29:56,280
you don't earn anything unless you perform.

751
00:29:56,281 --> 00:29:57,921
How do you pay for your living costs during those times?

752
00:29:58,551 --> 00:30:00,790
I think that's why I did many side jobs.

753
00:30:00,791 --> 00:30:02,720
- What kind?
- For example,

754
00:30:02,721 --> 00:30:04,490
I worked for H Mart...

755
00:30:04,491 --> 00:30:06,760
as a home appliance installation technician,

756
00:30:06,761 --> 00:30:09,900
and I also did night shifts to clean public bathhouses.

757
00:30:09,901 --> 00:30:11,930
- That's tough.
- Public bathhouses?

758
00:30:11,931 --> 00:30:14,400
I also sold cup rice at a U.S. military base.

759
00:30:14,401 --> 00:30:15,800
Cup rice?

760
00:30:15,801 --> 00:30:19,200
Most recently, I collected used clothing for about three years.

761
00:30:19,201 --> 00:30:22,041
I was able to quit that recently, thankfully.

762
00:30:22,371 --> 00:30:24,380
- You worked so hard.
- Yes.

763
00:30:24,381 --> 00:30:26,750
- You won 1st place.
- The Top 7 will perform now.

764
00:30:26,751 --> 00:30:28,880
- You have a concert, as well.
- They have their shows.

765
00:30:28,881 --> 00:30:30,050
- We have a national tour.
- Yes.

766
00:30:30,051 --> 00:30:33,450
Aren’t your band members worried?

767
00:30:33,451 --> 00:30:34,850
- That could be.
- Sure.

768
00:30:34,851 --> 00:30:36,791
But thankfully,

769
00:30:37,021 --> 00:30:39,930
they are telling me to enjoy everything.

770
00:30:39,931 --> 00:30:41,791
They are the smart ones.

771
00:30:42,061 --> 00:30:43,830
You need to succeed...

772
00:30:43,831 --> 00:30:45,260
- for the band to succeed.
- Yes.

773
00:30:45,261 --> 00:30:47,700
You will get more chances to perform afterwards.

774
00:30:47,701 --> 00:30:50,741
Kyung Hoon, did your members get upset...

775
00:30:50,941 --> 00:30:52,340
- when you got on Men on a Mission?
- On this show?

776
00:30:52,341 --> 00:30:53,341
They have no interest at all.

777
00:30:54,711 --> 00:30:56,410
And they don't even try to do these things.

778
00:30:56,411 --> 00:30:57,740
They won't do it.

779
00:30:57,741 --> 00:30:58,881
They don't want to get involved.

780
00:30:59,241 --> 00:31:00,710
Next is Jae Min.

781
00:31:00,711 --> 00:31:02,481
- Me?
- Jae Min is...

782
00:31:02,711 --> 00:31:04,751
We need to check on this, though.

783
00:31:05,621 --> 00:31:08,050
It says, "Acceptance to five applied music schools."

784
00:31:08,051 --> 00:31:10,360
- Right.
- They said this is incredible.

785
00:31:10,361 --> 00:31:11,760
There have been four acceptances before.

786
00:31:11,761 --> 00:31:13,190
- I heard that it was a first.
- Yes.

787
00:31:13,191 --> 00:31:14,330
I saw it on YouTube, as well.

788
00:31:14,331 --> 00:31:15,890
- It's a first.
- What are the four and five?

789
00:31:15,891 --> 00:31:18,600
Five acceptances are a first for men.

790
00:31:18,601 --> 00:31:20,030
Lee Mu Jin got accepted to four.

791
00:31:20,031 --> 00:31:21,031
- That's right.
- Yes.

792
00:31:21,032 --> 00:31:22,930
If you got five, what is the additional one?

793
00:31:22,931 --> 00:31:24,670
- Seoul Institute of the Arts, - Yes.

794
00:31:24,671 --> 00:31:26,441
Dong-Ah Institute of Media and Arts,

795
00:31:27,241 --> 00:31:30,081
Seokyeong University, Hongik University,

796
00:31:30,241 --> 00:31:31,680
and Howon University are the five.

797
00:31:31,681 --> 00:31:34,080
Among the five, which did you choose?

798
00:31:34,081 --> 00:31:35,280
I chose Seoul Institute of the Arts.

799
00:31:35,281 --> 00:31:37,421
Yes, we’re alumni.

800
00:31:38,521 --> 00:31:39,750
You didn't graduate.

801
00:31:39,751 --> 00:31:40,890
Are we not if I didn't graduate?

802
00:31:40,891 --> 00:31:42,550
- You got expelled.
- Come on.

803
00:31:42,551 --> 00:31:43,860
Are we not alumni...

804
00:31:43,861 --> 00:31:45,561
- if I didn't graduate?
- You got expelled, Sang Min.

805
00:31:45,761 --> 00:31:46,860
You didn't enroll.

806
00:31:46,861 --> 00:31:48,990
I did. I went for a year.

807
00:31:48,991 --> 00:31:50,200
- Hey.
- He didn't even enroll.

808
00:31:50,201 --> 00:31:52,260
- He did.
- I went for a year.

809
00:31:52,261 --> 00:31:53,830
I went for a year, and then I dropped out, you fool.

810
00:31:53,831 --> 00:31:55,430
- Drop out or expelled?
- I dropped out.

811
00:31:55,431 --> 00:31:57,100
As far as I know, you were expelled.

812
00:31:57,101 --> 00:31:58,771
What do you know?

813
00:31:59,441 --> 00:32:01,340
How would you know about me?

814
00:32:01,341 --> 00:32:03,510
He went to Dong-Ah Institute of Media and Arts.

815
00:32:03,511 --> 00:32:05,110
I told you. I enrolled.

816
00:32:05,111 --> 00:32:06,580
- I dropped out.
- I see.

817
00:32:06,581 --> 00:32:08,210
Then are we not alumni?

818
00:32:08,211 --> 00:32:09,550
- You're not.
- We call that...

819
00:32:09,551 --> 00:32:11,621
- a high school graduate.
- Wait a minute.

820
00:32:13,051 --> 00:32:14,790
- It's true.
- Yes, a high school graduate.

821
00:32:14,791 --> 00:32:16,820
But being expelled and dropping out is different.

822
00:32:16,821 --> 00:32:19,490
- Sure.
- That's what I was thinking.

823
00:32:19,491 --> 00:32:20,660
You got a scholarship?

824
00:32:20,661 --> 00:32:22,561
I didn't get a scholarship, but...

825
00:32:22,891 --> 00:32:25,100
- A department head...
- Did they call you?

826
00:32:25,101 --> 00:32:27,301
called me...

827
00:32:27,931 --> 00:32:29,571
and asked me where I was going to attend.

828
00:32:30,041 --> 00:32:31,800
- Did they ask that?
- He asked if I would enroll...

829
00:32:31,801 --> 00:32:32,970
if they gave me a scholarship.

830
00:32:32,971 --> 00:32:34,670
I did get that kind of call.

831
00:32:34,671 --> 00:32:37,541
Jae Min, that call from the head could be voice phishing.

832
00:32:38,181 --> 00:32:39,581
- Come on.
- Hey.

833
00:32:40,211 --> 00:32:41,780
- I'll be careful.
- Don't trust it.

834
00:32:41,781 --> 00:32:43,750
"Hello."

835
00:32:43,751 --> 00:32:44,950
"This is the head."

836
00:32:44,951 --> 00:32:46,250
"Will you come..."

837
00:32:46,251 --> 00:32:47,721
- "if we give you a scholarship?"
- Jae Min.

838
00:32:48,051 --> 00:32:50,090
Why was the judges' initial reaction not good?

839
00:32:50,091 --> 00:32:53,461
That was because I was overly confident.

840
00:32:54,061 --> 00:32:56,130
I even introduced myself as "Ambitious Singer,"

841
00:32:56,131 --> 00:32:58,460
and I was really full of confidence.

842
00:32:58,461 --> 00:32:59,701
- That's right.
- I really was.

843
00:32:59,761 --> 00:33:02,130
(I am "Ambitious Singer.")

844
00:33:02,131 --> 00:33:05,240
(Ever since I started doing music,)

845
00:33:05,241 --> 00:33:06,600
(I knew I would become big.)

846
00:33:06,601 --> 00:33:08,611
(He's too full of confidence.)

847
00:33:09,811 --> 00:33:11,181
(I didn't want to press it unless I really had to.)

848
00:33:11,311 --> 00:33:13,110
I had no idea they would take it that way.

849
00:33:13,111 --> 00:33:14,580
I saw the show, and...

850
00:33:14,581 --> 00:33:19,080
I saw it, and the rest of the people came as contestants,

851
00:33:19,081 --> 00:33:21,150
but with Jae Min, it felt like he was there to perform.

852
00:33:21,151 --> 00:33:22,151
That's right.

853
00:33:22,152 --> 00:33:23,890
He didn't seem to see them as judges,

854
00:33:23,891 --> 00:33:25,960
- Yes, but...
- but just as his audience.

855
00:33:25,961 --> 00:33:28,691
He was going like this when he first appeared,

856
00:33:29,191 --> 00:33:31,160
so I did say to myself,

857
00:33:31,161 --> 00:33:32,700
"If he turns out to be bad,"

858
00:33:32,701 --> 00:33:33,800
(What is he going to do if he's bad?)

859
00:33:33,801 --> 00:33:36,400
"it's going to be embarrassing for him."

860
00:33:36,401 --> 00:33:38,740
- But after seeing him perform, - He's the best.

861
00:33:38,741 --> 00:33:41,671
it all made sense.

862
00:33:41,771 --> 00:33:44,111
(He won approval from everyone after his first performance.)

863
00:33:44,411 --> 00:33:46,140
Even so, you should have stayed humble.

864
00:33:46,141 --> 00:33:47,280
It's justified confidence.

865
00:33:47,281 --> 00:33:48,810
Was it on purpose, Jae Min?

866
00:33:48,811 --> 00:33:50,221
You should have stayed humble, you punk.

867
00:33:51,151 --> 00:33:52,450
He could be humble,

868
00:33:52,451 --> 00:33:53,820
but if it's a tactic, then it's okay.

869
00:33:53,821 --> 00:33:56,690
Sure, but after seeing the show,

870
00:33:56,691 --> 00:33:58,561
my facial expressions and all...

871
00:33:58,661 --> 00:34:00,460
did not look too good, even for me.

872
00:34:00,461 --> 00:34:02,590
With the skills of the Top Seven,

873
00:34:02,591 --> 00:34:03,661
it's acceptable.

874
00:34:04,831 --> 00:34:05,831
Thank you.

875
00:34:06,231 --> 00:34:09,471
Next is slowly.

876
00:34:10,031 --> 00:34:11,540
She wrote "Whirlwind Transfer."

877
00:34:11,541 --> 00:34:13,200
- Yes.
- What does that mean?

878
00:34:13,201 --> 00:34:16,841
I used to attend another high school until the first year,

879
00:34:17,041 --> 00:34:18,880
then I transferred to School of Performing Arts Seoul,

880
00:34:18,881 --> 00:34:20,210
- which has the yellow uniform.
- I know.

881
00:34:20,211 --> 00:34:21,211
- It's a performing arts school.
- It's famous.

882
00:34:21,212 --> 00:34:22,950
I got accepted as a transfer student...

883
00:34:22,951 --> 00:34:24,250
after preparing for just two weeks.

884
00:34:24,251 --> 00:34:25,320
(She got accepted after 2 weeks of preparation.)

885
00:34:25,321 --> 00:34:28,220
Aren't a third of the students all celebrities?

886
00:34:28,221 --> 00:34:30,920
Yes, Jang Won Young...

887
00:34:30,921 --> 00:34:32,360
and Jung Kook went there.

888
00:34:32,361 --> 00:34:33,390
There are a lot of dancers, as well.

889
00:34:33,391 --> 00:34:34,830
Yes, a lot of dancers went there.

890
00:34:34,831 --> 00:34:37,130
- From Street Woman Fighter.
- I heard that...

891
00:34:37,131 --> 00:34:38,930
you were the youngest contestant?

892
00:34:38,931 --> 00:34:40,270
- Yes.
- How old are you?

893
00:34:40,271 --> 00:34:41,500
When we were filming,

894
00:34:41,501 --> 00:34:42,600
I was in...

895
00:34:42,601 --> 00:34:44,201
- my 12th grade in high school.
- You were?

896
00:34:44,871 --> 00:34:48,111
(That is when her ascent started.)

897
00:34:48,341 --> 00:34:49,770
I heard that you took the CSAT?

898
00:34:49,771 --> 00:34:51,510
Yes, I did,

899
00:34:51,511 --> 00:34:54,481
but I was preparing for Round Four.

900
00:34:54,851 --> 00:34:56,550
So I went to school...

901
00:34:56,551 --> 00:34:58,750
to take the test before the rehearsal.

902
00:34:58,751 --> 00:35:00,191
I guessed all the answers.

903
00:35:00,421 --> 00:35:01,720
What?

904
00:35:01,721 --> 00:35:03,821
So I think I got one correct answer.

905
00:35:04,161 --> 00:35:05,161
I had to do that.

906
00:35:05,162 --> 00:35:06,760
But it's not easy to get one right...

907
00:35:06,761 --> 00:35:08,190
- after guessing every question.
- Sure.

908
00:35:08,191 --> 00:35:10,730
- So how were the results?
- Did you get the score?

909
00:35:10,731 --> 00:35:12,900
I did, and I did not do well.

910
00:35:12,901 --> 00:35:14,031
Sure.

911
00:35:16,401 --> 00:35:20,171
(She shook off the stress from her CSAT exams on stage,)

912
00:35:22,011 --> 00:35:25,180
(and got All Again in Round 4.)

913
00:35:25,181 --> 00:35:26,610
- So today, - What will you sing for us today?

914
00:35:26,611 --> 00:35:28,511
- what will you sing?
- Today, to be honest...

915
00:35:28,551 --> 00:35:31,320
It hasn't been long since I taught myself how to play the guitar.

916
00:35:31,321 --> 00:35:34,120
At that time, I felt so happy to be playing,

917
00:35:34,121 --> 00:35:37,260
so I just thought I should play it on stage.

918
00:35:37,261 --> 00:35:40,661
I will sing Kang San Eh's "Pollack," which was my first stage.

919
00:35:40,891 --> 00:35:42,591
- "Pollack?"
- Gosh.

920
00:35:43,761 --> 00:35:44,761
- "Pollack?"
- Yes.

921
00:35:45,401 --> 00:35:46,930
Let's go, slowly.

922
00:35:46,931 --> 00:35:49,171
("Pollack" by slowly, original song by Kang San Eh)

923
00:35:49,331 --> 00:35:50,671
(It becomes blood)

924
00:36:06,921 --> 00:36:07,921
(Gosh...)

925
00:36:17,931 --> 00:36:18,931
(Hey!)

926
00:36:36,051 --> 00:36:37,150
Thank you for the meal.

927
00:36:37,151 --> 00:36:38,151
(Gosh)

928
00:37:20,561 --> 00:37:22,090
(Pollack)

929
00:37:22,091 --> 00:37:26,900
(Thank you)

930
00:37:26,901 --> 00:37:31,201
(For the meal)

931
00:37:32,501 --> 00:37:34,141
Thank you.

932
00:37:35,241 --> 00:37:36,241
(Hey!)

933
00:37:37,711 --> 00:37:39,380
(They had an amazing meal thanks to the pollack chef.)

934
00:37:39,381 --> 00:37:40,381
- That's good.
- Gosh.

935
00:37:40,981 --> 00:37:43,821
- That was tasty.
- I love it.

936
00:37:44,421 --> 00:37:46,521
(They are 100 percent full.)

937
00:37:47,391 --> 00:37:49,790
I was overwhelmed from the beginning.

938
00:37:49,791 --> 00:37:52,021
- It was amazing.
- It's like a grandpa.

939
00:37:52,821 --> 00:37:54,291
Next is Ye Chan.

940
00:37:54,591 --> 00:37:56,230
Ye Chan's background is...

941
00:37:56,231 --> 00:37:58,261
Yes. I thought so.

942
00:37:59,101 --> 00:38:00,400
It says, "Girl group."

943
00:38:00,401 --> 00:38:02,370
- That's right.
- Yes. Queen!

944
00:38:02,371 --> 00:38:04,370
Back in 2015,

945
00:38:04,371 --> 00:38:07,010
I had my debut with my team, Awesome Baby.

946
00:38:07,011 --> 00:38:11,410
And in 2018, I had a new debut in a group called "Pink Fantasy."

947
00:38:11,411 --> 00:38:14,351
- Twice?
- I was in a girl group twice.

948
00:38:14,651 --> 00:38:17,320
We weren't able to have an active promotion,

949
00:38:17,321 --> 00:38:18,620
so we didn't get paid in the end,

950
00:38:18,621 --> 00:38:20,491
and it wasn't easy...

951
00:38:20,751 --> 00:38:22,220
- during those times.
- Both times?

952
00:38:22,221 --> 00:38:25,160
How old were you when you first started training?

953
00:38:25,161 --> 00:38:27,991
I first started when I was 19.

954
00:38:28,491 --> 00:38:30,360
But you have the skills, Ye Chan.

955
00:38:30,361 --> 00:38:31,560
- That's right.
- Thank you.

956
00:38:31,561 --> 00:38:32,960
You were called by many groups.

957
00:38:32,961 --> 00:38:34,300
You would have been the main vocalist, right?

958
00:38:34,301 --> 00:38:36,030
- I was the main vocalist in both.
- Of course.

959
00:38:36,031 --> 00:38:39,701
In both groups. How much did you get paid?

960
00:38:39,941 --> 00:38:41,511
I got paid nothing.

961
00:38:42,171 --> 00:38:43,640
- So I...
- That's right.

962
00:38:43,641 --> 00:38:45,111
also worked part-time like Oh Ouk.

963
00:38:45,281 --> 00:38:47,210
- I delivered packages.
- Delivery.

964
00:38:47,211 --> 00:38:49,211
And I worked in a factory,

965
00:38:49,351 --> 00:38:50,450
a PC room,

966
00:38:50,451 --> 00:38:53,850
and until recently, I worked in a bbq restaurant.

967
00:38:53,851 --> 00:38:55,791
- Really?
- I worked at many places.

968
00:38:56,121 --> 00:38:58,161
She would have been really popular in the PC room.

969
00:38:59,091 --> 00:39:00,760
If the part-timer looks pretty,

970
00:39:00,761 --> 00:39:02,890
- many people go there, right?
- They didn't ask me for my number.

971
00:39:02,891 --> 00:39:05,900
I guess you went to the pc room a lot when the part-timer...

972
00:39:05,901 --> 00:39:08,131
- looked pretty.
- I would go there a lot.

973
00:39:09,031 --> 00:39:10,070
There are famous places.

974
00:39:10,071 --> 00:39:11,740
Even for billiard halls, I would go to the place...

975
00:39:11,741 --> 00:39:13,400
